---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Refund Policy" description="Refund Policy for whyismywebsiteslow.com.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Refund Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</p>

    <div class="prose prose-invert mt-8 max-w-none prose-p:text-slate-300 prose-li:text-slate-300 prose-headings:text-slate-100 prose-strong:text-slate-100">
      <p>
        This Refund Policy describes how refunds work for purchases made through whyismywebsiteslow.com. If you purchase
        through a payment provider (such as Paddle), the refund may be processed by that provider, but the policy below
        describes our intent and how to request help.
      </p>

      <h2>One-time purchases</h2>
      <p>
        If you purchase a one-time digital product (for example, a report unlock), and you experience an issue that
        prevents access to what you paid for, contact us and we’ll make it right—typically by fixing access or issuing a
        refund when appropriate.
      </p>

      <h2>Subscriptions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You can cancel a subscription to prevent future renewals.</li>
        <li>Where applicable, refund requests are evaluated case-by-case (for example, duplicate charges or billing errors).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Services</h2>
      <p>
        If you purchase a service (for example, implementation help), refund eligibility depends on the scope of work
        and whether work has begun. Any specific terms shown at checkout or in a written statement of work will control.
      </p>

      <h2>How to request a refund</h2>
      <p>
        Reply to the receipt email from your payment provider with your request and the reason. If you no longer have
        the receipt email, use the site to locate the appropriate contact route and include your order identifier so we
        can find the purchase.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

